# Lesson 1.4

# Memecoin Narratives

Memecoins usually follow **narrative categories**.

Recognizing narratives helps predict which coins may go viral.

Your guide identifies several major categories. 

---

## 1 — Animal & Cult Memes

Examples:

• dog coins
• penguin coins
• sigma/gigachad memes

These work because they are **instantly recognizable**.

---

## 2 — News & Politics

These coins follow current events.

Examples:

• Trump memes
• Elon memes
• sports events

They often pump quickly but fade fast.

---

## 3 — Internet Culture

Memes from online communities.

Examples:

• gaming culture
• absurd humor
• viral jokes

These spread through social platforms.

---

## 4 — AI Memes

Coins inspired by AI trends.

These combine **two narratives**:

AI hype + memes.

---

## 5 — Influencer / TikTok Memes

Coins tied to viral personalities.

If the creator goes viral, the coin follows.

---

## 6 — Beta Plays

Copies of successful memes.

Example:

Solana version of a famous Ethereum meme coin.

These sometimes perform well because they **ride an existing narrative**.

---

