# Lesson 1.5

# Realistic Expectations

Memecoin trading is **high risk**.

Most coins fail.

Your guide provides realistic statistics. 

---

## Memecoin Outcomes

Typical distribution:

70–80% → complete failures
15–20% → small winners
3–5% → big winners
<1% → massive winners

---

## The Memecoin Math

Example:

10 trades of $100 each.

Results:

7 failures → -$700
2 moderate wins → +$400
1 big win → +$3000

Total result:

$2600 profit.

One big winner pays for many losses.

---

## Risk Management Rules

Your guide suggests:

• never risk more than **1–2% per trade**
• diversify across many coins
• take profits early 

Profit strategy example:

2x → remove initial investment
3x → sell 25–50%
let the rest ride.

---

